docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON, May 28-- The climax of the Sixth International Philatelic Exhibition, which closes here Monday night, arrived tonight for hundreds of collectors when awards were presented at a dinner at the Shoreham Hotel, site of the show. It is the first exhibition of this type in Washington. Five previous international exhibitions in the United States were held in New York.

docs.lead_paragraph: BUENOS AIRES, May 28-- President Alfredo Stroessner of Paraguay dismissed all top police officials today in a scandal involving the disappearance of $400,000 and two West Germans alleged to be bank embezzlers.
